  "text": "Data completeness for the blood pressure measurements was high, with only 84 (2.8%) Wave 1 and 120 (3.6%) Wave 2 participants missing blood pressure measurements. Data completeness for covariates was similarly high, with most covariates having less than 5% missing data, while BMI had a slightly higher (6.3%) missingness. Multiple imputation with chained equations was used to handle all covariate and outcome variable missingness by creating ten datasets with complete data and pooling estimates across datasets [CITATION_1] .",
